Use a USB camera with your Android device in Webex Meetings
Connect a USB camera to your Android device for better picture quality and to prevent accidentally showing your surroundings. After you join a meeting, you can select your camera as the source video.
You can select your USB camera only after you join a meeting. Meetings supports any USB video device class (UVC protocol) compatible device.
During a meeting, tap Video > Camera settings, and select USB camera.